{"TopicId":184167,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9.1] BDArmory Continued v1.3.4 \u0026amp; BDArmory Multiplayer [17/09/2021]","CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-01T22:21:07Z","PageNum":15,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Space Man","CreatedById":73734,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T12:16:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot used this mod since game version 0.90. How do I make my AGM missiles lock onto debris and things that need blowing up but don\u0027t have a weapon/ai module?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Destroyer_Harekaze","CreatedById":203376,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T14:36:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223758183\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584527522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDAC is a functional mod, where other mods can add tons of weapons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is more or less just a stand in to show other modders \u0022yes you can have radar on a turret, which does launch missiles\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about increasing the number of missiles in the weapons manager?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0why does the autopilo register threats as 10E38 away when they have just charged at each other and overshoot?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did try that and it works, though at the same time I don\u2019t want the AI up to burn so many missiles against a single target in case of re-engagement. Hence why I used a limit of 3 missile/target while carrying 6 AIM-120s and 12 AIM-9s. Another way of doing it is to change the engagement style by bumping normal altitude higher and that seems to fix it too. Though it is frustrating for the weapons manager to not consider\u00A0AMRAAMs that have already missed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T23:30:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223758203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584533782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273734\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Space Man\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, The Space Man said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot used this mod since game version 0.90. How do I make my AGM missiles lock onto debris and things that need blowing up but don\u0027t have a weapon/ai module?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse a FLR targetting ball to manually lock on debris.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen fire your laser-guided agm while keeping target locked, or press the \u0022Send to GPS\u0022 button and fire you gps guided weapons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-19T04:10:41Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2020 04:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 19, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Xd the great\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-20T11:09:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0how do evasive manuvers work? My super manuverable plane cannot evade sidewinders lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd how do I buff flares so they can distract missiles better?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-20T11:21:03Z\u0022 title=\u002203/20/2020 11:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Xd the great\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP dogfight master","CreatedById":192818,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-22T22:07:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni was trying to use the rotary bomb rack to shoot missiles but it does not shoot the missiles out in the direction intended out towards the yellow arrow, instead, it shoots out away from it\u0027s original position. (first one works perfectly, second one shoots to the right, third one more to the right...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-22T23:55:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223759841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584914822\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192818\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSP dogfight master\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, KSP dogfight master said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni was trying to use the rotary bomb rack to shoot missiles but it does not shoot the missiles out in the direction intended out towards the yellow arrow, instead, it shoots out away from it\u0027s original position. (first one works perfectly, second one shoots to the right, third one more to the right...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, it seems buggy too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and judging by your name, I guess you are interested in this competition:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002290599\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed734326207\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/182084-air-superiority-fighter-competition-unlimited-reboot-for-ksp-16-and-bda-12/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-22T23:55:53Z\u0022 title=\u002203/22/2020 11:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Xd the great\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP dogfight master","CreatedById":192818,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-22T23:59:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223759861\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584921327\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, it seems buggy too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and judging by your name, I guess you are interested in this competition:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002290599\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9605010537\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/182084-air-superiority-fighter-competition-unlimited-reboot-for-ksp-16-and-bda-12/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlol that was my name like 2 years ago, thought it was cool... now it makes me sound like a d**k\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKurgan","CreatedById":164104,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-23T05:26:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223758927\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584702563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/20/2020 at 7:09 AM, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow do evasive manuvers work? My super manuverable plane cannot evade sidewinders lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter some research, I found out that dodging a modern, sort range, high speed, air to air missile is next to impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I made them all nearly impossible to dodge... not 100% impossible, but very near impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlares in low numbers are completely ineffective... true story.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlares are launched in mass quantities for a reason. My jets have at least 4 flare launchers... most of the time more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-23T05:27:28Z\u0022 title=\u002203/23/2020 05:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 23, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by TheKurgan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-23T06:32:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223759923\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584941193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164104\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheKurgan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, TheKurgan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter some research, I found out that dodging a modern, sort range, high speed, air to air missile is next to impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I made them all nearly impossible to dodge... not 100% impossible, but very near impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlares in low numbers are completely ineffective... true story.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlares are launched in mass quantities for a reason. My jets have at least 4 flare launchers... most of the time more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to outmaneuver one?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKurgan","CreatedById":164104,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-23T12:51:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have been building the most crazy maneuverable target drones for missile testing for the past 3 years... my drones can pull off 45G turns at will, and they can out maneuver a sidewinder about 2% of the time, and 0% against an AMRAAM.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is in a sandbox setting with g force limits on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CrayzeeMonkey","CreatedById":77712,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T00:23:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResults after working on ModuleMissileRearm while under quarantine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/vTmxkTmzFE4?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T02:37:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way for the camera trackers to still work while they\u0027re not on focus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T09:35:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760312\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585017445\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121059\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RurouniDonut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, RurouniDonut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way for the camera trackers to still work while they\u0027re not on focus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLasing? Probably not. You need to lase a target for hellfires and mavericks to hit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you can always transfer targeting info between gps/radar/lasing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760261\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585009393\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CrayzeeMonkey\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, CrayzeeMonkey said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nResults after working on ModuleMissileRearm while under quarantine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/vTmxkTmzFE4?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich mod is this? Bdac?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can imagine someone mounting these to planes and setting them to reload with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E action group.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEndless stream of missiles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CrayzeeMonkey","CreatedById":77712,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:15:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585042508\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich mod is this? Bdac?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ChippedChap/BDArmory/tree/feature_reload\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EIt is a fork of BDAC\u003C/a\u003E, yes. I\u0027m planning to add auto-reload so you don\u0027t have to use action groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:22:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585052153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CrayzeeMonkey\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, CrayzeeMonkey said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ChippedChap/BDArmory/tree/feature_reload\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EIt is a fork of BDAC\u003C/a\u003E, yes. I\u0027m planning to add auto-reload so you don\u0027t have to use action groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNicely done \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0I\u0027m happy to see someone implementing new things.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:23:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585042508\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLasing? Probably not. You need to lase a target for hellfires and mavericks to hit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you can always transfer targeting info between gps/radar/lasing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich mod is this? Bdac?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can imagine someone mounting these to planes and setting them to reload with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E action group.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEndless stream of missiles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDarn, that sucks. I just wanted to use the tracking camera for rocket launches to track them in window \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ewhile in IVA or something.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:29:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760418\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585052607\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121059\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RurouniDonut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, RurouniDonut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDarn, that sucks. I just wanted to use the tracking camera for rocket launches to track them in window \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Ewhile in IVA or something.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you mean something like this?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/G0iAlCGRI2E?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:30:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760419\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585052974\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you mean something like this?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/G0iAlCGRI2E?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E but is it possible perhaps to have the target window still up when you\u0027re controlling the rocket and not the tracker?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-24T12:34:57Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2020 12:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RurouniDonut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:32:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585052579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNicely done \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0I\u0027m happy to see someone implementing new things.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo will it be added in future versions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585052153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CrayzeeMonkey\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, CrayzeeMonkey said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ChippedChap/BDArmory/tree/feature_reload\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EIt is a fork of BDAC\u003C/a\u003E, yes. I\u0027m planning to add auto-reload so you don\u0027t have to use action groups.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and also I can see some dogfight competition runners\u00A0screaming no at the idea of accepting such rails into their competitions, so better add this as a new part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:35:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585053130\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo will it be added in future versions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a Pull Request is made and it works, of course \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585053056\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121059\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RurouniDonut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, RurouniDonut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will need to tweak the radar to have an increased locking range (I\u0027m using like 2000 km in that video) , you will need to change the camera tracking\u00A0 FOV resolutions to be able to continue zooming , increase the bdarmory settings ranges and attach a weapon manager to the rocket that you want to track.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way I have plans to create a separate mod to include just a tracking camera for rockets and satellite tracking\u00A0 using the BDArmory camera but without any logic regarding radar locking or anything related with BDArmory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-24T12:42:19Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2020 12:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by jrodriguez\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:43:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760423\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585053314\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf a Pull Request is made and it works, of course \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will need to tweak the radar to have an increased locking range (I\u0027m using like 2000 km in that video) , you will need to change the camera tracking\u00A0 FOV resolutions to be able to continue zooming in . Increase the bdarmory settings ranges and attach a weapon manager to the rocket that you want to track.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way I have plans to create a separate mod to include just a tracking camera for rockets and satellite tracking\u00A0 using the BDArmory camera but without any logic regarding radar locking or anything related with BDArmory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA separate mod would be awesome! Would love to be able to have the rocket being tracked in a separate window while controlling the launch! If I add a weapons manager to the rocket for now though, would that keep the tracking window up while I\u0027m controlling the rocket?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-24T12:43:57Z\u0022 title=\u002203/24/2020 12:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 24, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by RurouniDonut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760425\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585053826\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121059\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RurouniDonut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, RurouniDonut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA separate mod would be awesome! Would love to be able to have the rocket being tracked in a separate window while controlling the launch! If I add a weapons manager to the rocket for now though, would that keep the tracking window up while I\u0027m controlling the rocket?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuhm as you can see on the video. I\u0027m not really controlling the rocket, the rocket is controlled by itself (mechjeb) I\u0027m only acting as an spectator, enjoying a beautiful and success launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:50:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760428\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585054083\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuhm as you can see on the video. I\u0027m not really controlling the rocket, the rocket is controlled by itself (mechjeb) I\u0027m only acting as an spectator, enjoying a beautiful and success launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was thinking you might need to control it if there\u0027s a problem that arises during launch but I guess you can switch to the vessel fast hopefully.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T12:54:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585054218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121059\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RurouniDonut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, RurouniDonut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was thinking you might need to control it if there\u0027s a problem that arises during launch but I guess you can switch to the vessel fast hopefully.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but if you switch you will not be able to see the camera tracking window\u00A0(this is because the camera tracking window is bound to the vessel that has the camera tracking module)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RurouniDonut","CreatedById":121059,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-24T13:00:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223760432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022184167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221585054466\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but if you switch you will not be able to see the camera tracking window\u00A0(this is because the camera tracking window is bound to the vessel that has the camera tracking module)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhh okay, there\u0027s no way atm to add the tracking module to the rocket I imagine then? If not, hopefully I can switch fast enough \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}